Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["KnoodleIdentify", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"36b112fe-6bd3-4a68-bcfa-98f1bef159f2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell["   ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->"137a2f90-4602-4040-8655-44a6973ea35a"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"KnoodleIdentify", "[", 
   StyleBox["input", "TI"], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",ExpressionUUID->
  "2caeb38f-8115-4983-955f-76ae836d8666"],
 "\[LineSeparator]identifies the knot type of a knot diagram by looking it up \
in Knoodle's knot lookup table (KLUT)."
}], "Usage",ExpressionUUID->"2564e344-b2bc-47e6-8d42-e19afa49fd01"],

Cell["\<\
KnoodleIdentify returns an Association from each identified prime summand, a \
KnotSymbol[c, i, alternating, coset], to its integer multiplicity. A connect \
sum of several prime knots gives one entry per distinct prime factor, with \
the factor's multiplicity as the value. The unknot gives <||>, the empty \
association: an unknot summand is the identity element for connect sum, so it \
is simply omitted.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"848bd494-3644-4f04-b2e8-5f74f3841214"],

Cell["\<\
input accepts the same representations as KnoodleDraw. The lookup is \
self-contained: it decomposes and simplifies internally, so input need not be \
simplified first.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"67269e44-6dc8-49d2-bc91-c9b1a930f19c"],

Cell["\<\
A summand with more crossings than the lookup table covers comes back as \
Unidentified[n, pd] -> multiplicity, where pd is the summand's own signed PD \
code, for offline analysis. A summand inside the table's range that still \
fails to resolve comes back as NotFound[n, pd] -> multiplicity instead.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"3e94bcad-0ff9-44a7-b484-a1826a76c5e0"],

Cell["\<\
KnoodleIdentify only identifies knots. A genuine link (more than one \
component) fails with $Failed and a KnoodleIdentify::link message; apply \
KnoodleSimplify with \"Unite\" -> True first if the components should be \
treated as connect-summed into a single knot.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"5a64c57f-9552-4bdb-bd2b-c2b7afdf7e56"],

Cell["\<\
3D geometry is randomly rotated before being projected to a diagram, as in \
KnoodleDraw and KnoodleSimplify -- without this a highly symmetric curve can \
hit a degenerate projection and fail. Set \"RandomizeProjection\" -> False \
for the plain z-axis projection; if the projection then degenerates, \
KnoodleIdentify returns $Failed with a KnoodleIdentify::failed message.\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"13d8f336-e029-4bc6-8e08-26c65d874275"],

Cell["The following options can be given:", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"415133f3-2915-4a18-8aff-5d88ea6e0c6e"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "d8b0a2d5-d246-4c6d-a744-0f12d63e762d"], "\"\<MaxCrossings\>\"", 
    "Automatic", Cell["\<\
restrict the lookup to subtables with at most this many crossings (3 to 13); \
Automatic is the table's full range. Knots above a restricted range come back \
as NotFound.\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"1148cc12-6dfc-43b7-ba45-defe046c5fd6"]},
   {Cell["      ", "ModInfo",ExpressionUUID->
     "43b34dd5-27f6-4d09-b095-134c2248addd"], "\"\<RandomizeProjection\>\"", 
    "True", Cell["\<\
randomly rotate 3D input before projecting, avoiding degenerate projections; \
set False for reproducibility\
\>", "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"2fe754d9-07a8-431b-bf4a-fb93e1d4a219"]}
  }]], "3ColumnTableMod",ExpressionUUID->"3e9deb5b-16fd-461e-b166-\
48f82dc786d8"]
}, Open  ]],

